Name: YCCP Bird Area Searches
Description: This study area in Yolo County includes 10 200-m long area search plots along revegetated riparian edges and hedgerows in farm and ranch landscapes.  They are restoration sites implemented by the Yolo Creek and Community Partnership (Yolo Co. RCD, Center for Land-Based Learning, Putah Creek Council, and Audubon CA, and this is part of a 3-yr. evaluation of the wildlife habitat benefits provided by these projects.  The projects and this monitoring by Point Blue are funded by the Yocha Dehe Community Fund.
